LAST 7 DAYS TOP STORIES
------------------------------------------------------------
PEMEX  ENCOUNTERS NATURAL GAS DEVELOPMENT OPPOSITON 
Pemex runs into opposition on plans to raise the foriegn investment
capital needed to for natural gas development plans
  http://www.rigzone.com/news/article.asp?a_id=2284

KINDER MORGAN BUYS TEJAS
Kinder Morgan Energy Partners LP of Houston entered into an agreement to
purchase Tejas Gas LLC for approximately $750 million in cash.
  http://www.rigzone.com/news/article.asp?a_id=2286

NEXEN SETS NEXT YEARS BUDGET 
Nexen's new capital budget is 1.24 billion dollars. About $240 million is
scheduled for worldwide exploaration projects.
  http://www.rigzone.com/news/article.asp?a_id=2283

PATTERSON/UTI ENERGY, INC  BUYS CLERE DRILLING COMPANY ASSETS
PATTERSON-UTI ENERGY, INC. the second-largest operator of land-based oil
and natural gas drilling rigs in North America, today announced the
acquisition of 17 land-based drilling rigs from Cleere Drilling Company

  http://www.rigzone.com/news/article.asp?a_id=2281

ONGC AND UK BASED  BG GROUP DISCUSS ENRON PROPERTIES
India's state-run Oil and Natural Gas Corp remains open to continued
discussions with UK's BG Group over the operatorship of the Panna-Mukta
and Tapti oil and gas fields offshore western India
  http://www.rigzone.com/news/article.asp?a_id=2279

PETRONAS PROJECTS RATES FOR SOUTH CHINA SEA ANGSI FIELD 
Malaysia's state-owned Petronas expects the Angsi oil field in the South
China Sea to produce 65,000 b/d of oil and 450-mil cu ft/day of natural
gas at its peak.
  http://www.rigzone.com/news/article.asp?a_id=2280

REPSOL OFFSHORE EXPLORATORY LICENSES TOO CLOSE TO MORROCCO
Morocco has denounced Spain's violation of the country's maritime
territory after Madrid distributed offshore oil prospection licenses for
the Canary Islands in Moroccan controlled seas.

 

  http://www.rigzone.com/news/article.asp?a_id=2285

DELTA PETROLEUM TO BUY PIPER PETROLEUM
Delta Petroleum Corporation, an independent energy exploration and
development company, has entered into an agreement to purchase Piper
Petroleum Company, a privately owned oil and gas company headquartered in
Fort Worth, Texas.
  http://www.rigzone.com/news/article.asp?a_id=2288

